{
    "name": "Sea Snake",
    "type": "creature",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Sea Snake",
            "type": "section",
            "text": "These lithe snakes like to frequent the shallow waters of tropical seas. Their 4-foot-long, blue-green bodies easily blend into the water where they lurk to ambush prey. Sea snakes are highly venomous but often choose not to inject their venom when biting, so encounters with them rarely result in fatalities.   \n  \nTales speak of massive sea snakes that swim in deeper waters and stalk ships, waiting for sailors to fall overboard or even climbing over the side to snatch them from the deck.",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Monster Core 2",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Monster Core 2 pg. 294",
                        "alt": "Monster Core 2 pg. 294",
                        "game-obj": "Sources",
                        "aonid": 276
                    },
                    "page": 294
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Snake",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Eating Habits",
                    "type": "section",
                    "text": "Snakes of all sorts eat their meals by devouring their prey whole. After incapacitating a creature, a snake unhinges its jaw and consumes the creature entirely, even if it\u2019s more than twice the diameter of the snake\u2019s body. A snake can consume a creature of the same size as itself or smaller, but most snakes are sluggish while the meal digests.",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Monster Core",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Monster Core pg. 316",
                                "alt": "Monster Core pg. 316",
                                "game-obj": "Sources",
                                "aonid": 221
                            },
                            "page": 316,
                            "errata": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "1.1",
                                "alt": "1.1",
                                "game-obj": "Sources",
                                "aonid": 221
                            }
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Additional Lore",
                        "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "name": "Snake Resources",
                    "type": "section",
                    "text": "Snakeskin's distinctive pattern and wide variety of applications make it a sought-after resource, and the hides of extra-large snakes like giant anacondas can fetch a fine price in the right market. Such oversized snake hides can be used to craft clothing of snakeskin leather, including boots and gloves, as well as other items such as scabbards, backpacks, and even tents or makeshift boats. A snake's hide can be cleanly removed with a successful Crafting check or appropriate Lore check",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Monster Core",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Monster Core pg. 316",
                                "alt": "Monster Core pg. 316",
                                "game-obj": "Sources",
                                "aonid": 221
                            },
                            "page": 316,
                            "errata": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "1.1",
                                "alt": "1.1",
                                "game-obj": "Sources",
                                "aonid": 221
                            }
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "treasure_and_rewards",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Treasure and Rewards",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Treasure and Rewards",
                        "image": "Sidebar_5_TreasureAndRewards.png"
                    },
                    "links": [
                        {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Crafting",
                            "alt": "Crafting",
                            "game-obj": "Skills",
                            "aonid": 37
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Lore",
                            "alt": "Lore",
                            "game-obj": "Skills",
                            "aonid": 41
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "name": "Snakes in Mythology",
                    "type": "section",
                    "text": "Snakes appear frequently and prominently in the myths and legends of many cultures throughout the Inner Sea region. In Ancient Osirion, snakes were revered and associated both with the serpent god Apep and the goddess Wadjet, the Green Empress. Perhaps the best-known example of snakes in Golarion's legends are the serpentfolk, serpentine humanoids who ruled vast swaths of the world in prehistoric times and worshiped a foul snake deity called Ydersius.",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Monster Core",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Monster Core pg. 316",
                                "alt": "Monster Core pg. 316",
                                "game-obj": "Sources",
                                "aonid": 221
                            },
                            "page": 316,
                            "errata": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "1.1",
                                "alt": "1.1",
                                "game-obj": "Sources",
                                "aonid": 221
                            }
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Additional Lore",
                        "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png"
                    },
                    "links": [
                        {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Wadjet",
                            "alt": "Wadjet",
                            "game-obj": "Deities",
                            "aonid": 62
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "serpentfolk",
                            "alt": "serpentfolk",
                            "game-obj": "MonsterFamilies",
                            "aonid": 468
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Ydersius",
                            "alt": "Ydersius",
                            "game-obj": "Deities",
                            "aonid": 211
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ],
            "text": "Snakes come in an array of forms, from jungle-dwelling constrictors that wrap around their prey to venomous vipers with deadly bites. Regardless, all snakes consume their prey whole by unhinging their jaws and using powerful muscles to move the food down their throats and into their stomachs.",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Monster Core",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Monster Core pg. 316",
                        "alt": "Monster Core pg. 316",
                        "game-obj": "Sources",
                        "aonid": 221
                    },
                    "page": 316,
                    "errata": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "1.1",
                        "alt": "1.1",
                        "game-obj": "Sources",
                        "aonid": 221
                    }
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
